org.apache.flex.compiler.projects

Interface IASProject

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ICompilerProject
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IFlexProject
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ASProject, FlexJSProject, FlexProject

    public interface IASProject
extends ICompilerProject
    Base interface for all project types that use a source manager and library manager to create ICompilationUnits.

      • setLibraries

        void setLibraries(List<File> libraries)
        The libraries used to compile source files in a project. The order of the libraries sets the priority of class definitions when name and the timestamp of a class are equal. Libraries at the beginning of the list have a higher priority than libraries at the end of the list.
        Parameters:
        libraries - The libraries in priority order, may not be null.

      • getLibraries

        The libraries available to compiler source in this project.
        Returns:
        the libraries are returned in priority order from highest to lowest. The list may not be modified.

      • createInvisibleCompilationUnit

        IInvisibleCompilationUnit createInvisibleCompilationUnit(String absoluteFileName,
                                                       IFileSpecificationGetter fileSpecGetter)
        Creates an IInvisibleCompilationUnit for the specified absolute file name.
        Parameters:
        absoluteFileName - The name of the file to create an IInvisibleCompilationUnit for.
        fileSpecGetter - A IFileSpecificationGetter that can be used by the new IInvisibleCompilationUnit to open files.
        Returns:
        A new IInvisibleCompilationUnit or null if the specified. file name is not found on the current source path of this IASProject.

      • createInvisibleCompilationUnit

        IInvisibleCompilationUnit createInvisibleCompilationUnit(String rootSourceFile,
                                                       IFileSpecificationGetter fileSpecGetter,
                                                       String qName)
        Creates an IInvisibleCompilationUnit for the specified absolute file name, specifying a qualified name. This version of createInvisibleCompilationUnit() is called when creating a IInvisibleCompilationUnit for a source file which isn't contained within the source path, as the qualified name of the IInvisibleCompilationUnit to be created can't be computed automatically. This happens when creating a IInvisibleCompilationUnit for an external file.
        Parameters:
        rootSourceFile - The name of the file to create an IInvisibleCompilationUnit for.
        fileSpecGetter - A IFileSpecificationGetter that can be used by the new IInvisibleCompilationUnit to open files.
        qName - The qualified name of the IInvisibleCompilationUnit
        Returns:
        A new IInvisibleCompilationUnit or null if the specified. file name is not found on the current source path of this IASProject.

      • isSupportedSourceFileType

        boolean isSupportedSourceFileType(String fileExtension)
        Determines if the specified file extension ( without the dot eg: as, not .as ) corresponds to a source file type that this project can create ICompilationUnits for.
        Parameters:
        fileExtension - The file extension to check without a dot, for example mxml.
        Returns:
        true if the file type associated with the specified file extension is supported by this project, false otherwise.
